    <title>Establishing the Select Committee on White Supremacy and Domestic Terror Movements.</title>
    <createDate>2017-09-14T03:11:18Z</createDate>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <actionDate>2017-09-13</actionDate>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-11-14T22:16:04Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Establishes the House Select Committee on White Supremacy, Nazism, and Domestic Terror Movements to investigate and report on:</p> <ul> <li> the increase in violence and threats carried out by white supremacist and neo-Nazi groups;</li> <li>the dangers presented to Jewish Americans, Muslim Americans, African Americans, Asian Pacific Americans, Latino Americans, LGBTQ Americans, and other Americans;</li> <li>ongoing efforts by the federal government to protect the rights of those targeted by white supremacist and neo-Nazi groups;</li> <li>the impact of such groups' threats to the security, health, and well-being of targeted groups, including children;</li> <li>the availability of funding to prevent violence and other threats to security by white supremacist groups; and </li> <li>the adequacy of laws to address the threats posed by white supremacists and neo-Nazi groups.</li></ul>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-09-13T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
